    "passives": {
      "PlanAPassiveAElminaModernBoss": {
        "id": "PlanAPassiveAElminaModernBoss",
        "found": true,
        "localization": {
          "name": "Cyber Creations",
          "description": "This unit is not affected by stun effects.\n\nThis unit will gain a Charge each time it attacks and does not defeat any non-conjured enemies.\n\nWhen this unit enters battle:\n- If this unit is not conjured, it will have Hold Ground (If this unit would be defeated by an enemy attack or a status effect while having more than 1 HP, it instead survives with 1 HP).\n- If this unit is conjured, this unit will Endure the next damage that would defeat it with 1HP. Endure effects cannot stack.\n\nWhenever this unit defeats any number of non-conjured enemies with an attack:\n- An Elmina will be added to the front of allied reinforcements. This effect cannot trigger if there are 8 or more \"Elmina, Moonveiled Agent\" in the ally team.\n- Then all charges are removed from this unit.\n\nCertain skills are affected by and may consume charges. A unit can store up to 3 charges and all charges are removed from a unit that leaves the battlefield. All Elmina's created by this unit will have matching Levels, Limit Breaks, Awakenings, Boosts, Potential, Mastery, Weapons, and Accessories."
        }
      },
      "PlanBPassiveAElminaModernBoss": {
        "id": "PlanBPassiveAElminaModernBoss",
        "found": true,
        "localization": {
          "name": "Hyper Speed",
          "description": "Triggered the first time this unit takes damage from an attack and survives until after the end of the turn, and when this unit activates Elmina Unleashed:\n- All allies will be Purified (any negative status effects like sleep, burn or poison are removed).\n- Then all other ally units will be given the next turns by having their TU reduced. Active skills that grant turns cannot be used by those allies until after they have had the turn.\n\nThese effects will each only trigger once each time this unit is on the battlefield, and only if this unit entered the battlefield from reinforcements.\n\nEach time this unit damages at least one enemy with an attack and leaves them on or below 10% of max HP (even if they are defeated by the attack), this unit will get another turn. Damaged targets cannot trigger this effect again until TU advances.\n\nEffects that influence TU order may interrupt extra turns (e.g. Stuns targeting the lowest TU target)."
        }
      }
    },
